{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk today about --"},{"time":3000,"text":"I've been asked to take the long view, and I'm going to tell you what"},{"time":9000,"text":"I think are the three biggest problems for humanity"},{"time":13000,"text":"from this long point of view."},{"time":16000,"text":"Some of these have already been touched upon by other speakers,"},{"time":19000,"text":"which is encouraging."},{"time":21000,"text":"It seems that there's not just one person"},{"time":23000,"text":"who thinks that these problems are important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"The first is -- death is a big problem."},{"time":29000,"text":"If you look at the statistics,"},{"time":32000,"text":"the odds are not very favorable to us."},{"time":34000,"text":"So far, most people who have lived have also died."},{"time":38000,"text":"Roughly 90 percent of everybody who has been alive has died by now."},{"time":42000,"text":"So the annual death rate adds up to 150,000 --"},{"time":48000,"text":"sorry, the daily death rate -- 150,000 people per day,"},{"time":51000,"text":"which is a huge number by any standard."},{"time":54000,"text":"The annual death rate, then, becomes 56 million."},{"time":59000,"text":"If we just look at the single, biggest cause of death -- aging --"},{"time":65000,"text":"it accounts for roughly two-thirds of all human people who die."},{"time":70000,"text":"That adds up to an annual death toll"},{"time":73000,"text":"of greater than the population of Canada."},{"time":75000,"text":"Sometimes, we don't see a problem"},{"time":77000,"text":"because either it's too familiar or it's too big."},{"time":81000,"text":"Can't see it because it's too big."},{"time":83000,"text":"I think death might be both too familiar and too big"},{"time":86000,"text":"for most people to see it as a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Once you think about it, you see this is not statistical points;"},{"time":91000,"text":"these are -- let's see, how far have I talked?"},{"time":93000,"text":"I've talked for three minutes."},{"time":96000,"text":"So that would be, roughly, 324 people have died since I've begun speaking."},{"time":103000,"text":"People like -- it's roughly the population in this room has just died."},{"time":108000,"text":"Now, the human cost of that is obvious,"},{"time":110000,"text":"once you start to think about it -- the suffering, the loss --"},{"time":113000,"text":"it's also, economically, enormously wasteful."},{"time":116000,"text":"I just look at the information, and knowledge, and experience"},{"time":119000,"text":"that is lost due to natural causes of death in general,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and aging, in particular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"Suppose we approximated one person with one book?"},{"time":127000,"text":"Now, of course, this is an underestimation."},{"time":129000,"text":"A person's lifetime of learning and experience"},{"time":135000,"text":"is a lot more than you could put into a single book."},{"time":137000,"text":"But let's suppose we did this."},{"time":140000,"text":"52 million people die of natural causes each year"},{"time":145000,"text":"corresponds, then, to 52 million volumes destroyed."},{"time":149000,"text":"Library of Congress holds 18 million volumes."},{"time":153000,"text":"We are upset about the burning of the Library of Alexandria."},{"time":156000,"text":"It's one of the great cultural tragedies"},{"time":158000,"text":"that we remember, even today."},{"time":162000,"text":"But this is the equivalent of three Libraries of Congress --"},{"time":164000,"text":"burnt down, forever lost -- each year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So that's the first big problem."},{"time":169000,"text":"And I wish Godspeed to Aubrey de Grey,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and other people like him,"},{"time":174000,"text":"to try to do something about this as soon as possible."},{"time":178000,"text":"Existential risk -- the second big problem."},{"time":181000,"text":"Existential risk is a threat to human survival, or to the long-term potential of our species."},{"time":188000,"text":"Now, why do I say that this is a big problem?"},{"time":190000,"text":"Well, let's first look at the probability --"},{"time":194000,"text":"and this is very, very difficult to estimate --"},{"time":197000,"text":"but there have been only four studies on this in recent years,"},{"time":200000,"text":"which is surprising."},{"time":202000,"text":"You would think that it would be of some interest"},{"time":205000,"text":"to try to find out more about this given that the stakes are so big,"},{"time":209000,"text":"but it's a very neglected area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"But there have been four studies --"},{"time":213000,"text":"one by John Lesley, wrote a book on this."},{"time":215000,"text":"He estimated a probability that we will fail"},{"time":217000,"text":"to survive the current century: 50 percent."},{"time":220000,"text":"Similarly, the Astronomer Royal, whom we heard speak yesterday,"},{"time":225000,"text":"also has a 50 percent probability estimate."},{"time":228000,"text":"Another author doesn't give any numerical estimate,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but says the probability is significant that it will fail."},{"time":234000,"text":"I wrote a long paper on this."},{"time":237000,"text":"I said assigning a less than 20 percent probability would be a mistake"},{"time":241000,"text":"in light of the current evidence we have."},{"time":244000,"text":"Now, the exact figures here,"},{"time":246000,"text":"we should take with a big grain of salt,"},{"time":248000,"text":"but there seems to be a consensus that the risk is substantial."},{"time":251000,"text":"Everybody who has looked at this and studied it agrees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"Now, if we think about what just reducing"},{"time":256000,"text":"the probability of human extinction by just one percentage point --"},{"time":261000,"text":"not very much -- so that's equivalent to 60 million lives saved,"},{"time":266000,"text":"if we just count the currently living people, the current generation."},{"time":270000,"text":"Now one percent of six billion people is equivalent to 60 million."},{"time":274000,"text":"So that's a large number."},{"time":276000,"text":"If we were to take into account future generations"},{"time":279000,"text":"that will never come into existence if we blow ourselves up,"},{"time":284000,"text":"then the figure becomes astronomical."},{"time":287000,"text":"If we could eventually colonize a chunk of the universe --"},{"time":290000,"text":"the Virgo supercluster --"},{"time":292000,"text":"maybe it will take us 100 million years to get there,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but if we go extinct we never will."},{"time":297000,"text":"Then, even a one percentage point reduction"},{"time":300000,"text":"in the extinction risk could be equivalent"},{"time":304000,"text":"to this astronomical number -- 10 to the power of 32."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307000,"text":"So if you take into account future generations as much as our own,"},{"time":311000,"text":"every other moral imperative of philanthropic cost just becomes irrelevant."},{"time":316000,"text":"The only thing you should focus on"},{"time":318000,"text":"would be to reduce existential risk"},{"time":320000,"text":"because even the tiniest decrease in existential risk"},{"time":324000,"text":"would just overwhelm any other benefit you could hope to achieve."},{"time":328000,"text":"And even if you just look at the current people,"},{"time":330000,"text":"and ignore the potential that would be lost if we went extinct,"},{"time":335000,"text":"it should still have a high priority."},{"time":337000,"text":"Now, let me spend the rest of my time on the third big problem,"},{"time":342000,"text":"because it's more subtle and perhaps difficult to grasp."},{"time":348000,"text":"Think about some time in your life --"},{"time":352000,"text":"some people might never have experienced it -- but some people,"},{"time":355000,"text":"there are just those moments that you have experienced"},{"time":358000,"text":"where life was fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"It might have been at the moment of some great, creative inspiration"},{"time":367000,"text":"you might have had when you just entered this flow stage."},{"time":369000,"text":"Or when you understood something you had never done before."},{"time":371000,"text":"Or perhaps in the ecstasy of romantic love."},{"time":375000,"text":"Or an aesthetic experience -- a sunset or a great piece of art."},{"time":380000,"text":"Every once in a while we have these moments,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and we realize just how good life can be when it's at its best."},{"time":386000,"text":"And you wonder, why can't it be like that all the time?"},{"time":391000,"text":"You just want to cling onto this."},{"time":393000,"text":"And then, of course, it drifts back into ordinary life and the memory fades."},{"time":397000,"text":"And it's really difficult to recall, in a normal frame of mind,"},{"time":401000,"text":"just how good life can be at its best."},{"time":404000,"text":"Or how bad it can be at its worst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"The third big problem is that life isn't usually"},{"time":410000,"text":"as wonderful as it could be."},{"time":412000,"text":"I think that's a big, big problem."},{"time":416000,"text":"It's easy to say what we don't want."},{"time":419000,"text":"Here are a number of things that we don't want --"},{"time":422000,"text":"illness, involuntary death, unnecessary suffering, cruelty,"},{"time":425000,"text":"stunted growth, memory loss, ignorance, absence of creativity."},{"time":431000,"text":"Suppose we fixed these things -- we did something about all of these."},{"time":434000,"text":"We were very successful."},{"time":436000,"text":"We got rid of all of these things."},{"time":438000,"text":"We might end up with something like this,"},{"time":441000,"text":"which is -- I mean, it's a heck of a lot better than that."},{"time":445000,"text":"But is this really the best we can dream of?"},{"time":450000,"text":"Is this the best we can do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"Or is it possible to find something a little bit more inspiring to work towards?"},{"time":458000,"text":"And if we think about this,"},{"time":460000,"text":"I think it's very clear that there are ways"},{"time":464000,"text":"in which we could change things, not just by eliminating negatives,"},{"time":467000,"text":"but adding positives."},{"time":469000,"text":"On my wish list, at least, would be:"},{"time":471000,"text":"much longer, healthier lives, greater subjective well-being,"},{"time":476000,"text":"enhanced cognitive capacities, more knowledge and understanding,"},{"time":481000,"text":"unlimited opportunity for personal growth"},{"time":483000,"text":"beyond our current biological limits, better relationships,"},{"time":487000,"text":"an unbounded potential for spiritual, moral"},{"time":489000,"text":"and intellectual development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"If we want to achieve this, what, in the world, would have to change?"},{"time":499000,"text":"And this is the answer -- we would have to change."},{"time":504000,"text":"Not just the world around us, but we, ourselves."},{"time":507000,"text":"Not just the way we think about the world, but the way we are -- our very biology."},{"time":511000,"text":"Human nature would have to change."},{"time":513000,"text":"Now, when we think about changing human nature,"},{"time":515000,"text":"the first thing that comes to mind"},{"time":517000,"text":"are these human modification technologies --"},{"time":521000,"text":"growth hormone therapy, cosmetic surgery,"},{"time":523000,"text":"stimulants like Ritalin, Adderall, anti-depressants,"},{"time":526000,"text":"anabolic steroids, artificial hearts."},{"time":528000,"text":"It's a pretty pathetic list."},{"time":531000,"text":"They do great things for a few people"},{"time":533000,"text":"who suffer from some specific condition,"},{"time":535000,"text":"but for most people, they don't really transform"},{"time":540000,"text":"what it is to be human."},{"time":542000,"text":"And they also all seem a little bit --"},{"time":544000,"text":"most people have this instinct that, well, sure,"},{"time":547000,"text":"there needs to be anti-depressants for the really depressed people."},{"time":549000,"text":"But there's a kind of queasiness"},{"time":551000,"text":"that these are unnatural in some way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"It's worth recalling that there are a lot of other"},{"time":556000,"text":"modification technologies and enhancement technologies that we use."},{"time":559000,"text":"We have skin enhancements, clothing."},{"time":563000,"text":"As far as I can see, all of you are users of this"},{"time":567000,"text":"enhancement technology in this room, so that's a great thing."},{"time":572000,"text":"Mood modifiers have been used from time immemorial --"},{"time":575000,"text":"caffeine, alcohol, nicotine, immune system enhancement,"},{"time":580000,"text":"vision enhancement, anesthetics --"},{"time":582000,"text":"we take that very much for granted,"},{"time":584000,"text":"but just think about how great progress that is --"},{"time":588000,"text":"like, having an operation before anesthetics was not fun."},{"time":592000,"text":"Contraceptives, cosmetics and brain reprogramming techniques --"},{"time":598000,"text":"that sounds ominous,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"but the distinction between what is a technology --"},{"time":604000,"text":"a gadget would be the archetype --"},{"time":606000,"text":"and other ways of changing and rewriting human nature is quite subtle."},{"time":610000,"text":"So if you think about what it means to learn arithmetic or to learn to read,"},{"time":614000,"text":"you're actually, literally rewriting your own brain."},{"time":617000,"text":"You're changing the microstructure of your brain as you go along."},{"time":621000,"text":"So in a broad sense, we don't need to think about technology"},{"time":624000,"text":"as only little gadgets, like these things here,"},{"time":626000,"text":"but even institutions and techniques,"},{"time":630000,"text":"psychological methods and so forth."},{"time":632000,"text":"Forms of organization can have a profound impact on human nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"Looking ahead, there is a range of technologies"},{"time":639000,"text":"that are almost certain to be developed sooner or later."},{"time":642000,"text":"We are very ignorant about what the time scale for these things are,"},{"time":646000,"text":"but they all are consistent with everything we know"},{"time":648000,"text":"about physical laws, laws of chemistry, etc."},{"time":652000,"text":"It's possible to assume,"},{"time":654000,"text":"setting aside a possibility of catastrophe,"},{"time":657000,"text":"that sooner or later we will develop all of these."},{"time":660000,"text":"And even just a couple of these would be enough"},{"time":663000,"text":"to transform the human condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"So let's look at some of the dimensions of human nature"},{"time":670000,"text":"that seem to leave room for improvement."},{"time":673000,"text":"Health span is a big and urgent thing,"},{"time":675000,"text":"because if you're not alive,"},{"time":677000,"text":"then all the other things will be to little avail."},{"time":680000,"text":"Intellectual capacity -- let's take that box,"},{"time":682000,"text":"which falls into a lot of different sub-categories:"},{"time":687000,"text":"memory, concentration, mental energy, intelligence, empathy."},{"time":690000,"text":"These are really great things."},{"time":692000,"text":"Part of the reason why we value these traits"},{"time":694000,"text":"is that they make us better at competing with other people --"},{"time":698000,"text":"they're positional goods."},{"time":700000,"text":"But part of the reason --"},{"time":702000,"text":"and that's the reason why we have ethical ground for pursuing these --"},{"time":706000,"text":"is that they're also intrinsically valuable."},{"time":709000,"text":"It's just better to be able to understand more of the world around you"},{"time":713000,"text":"and the people that you are communicating with,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and to remember what you have learned."},{"time":719000,"text":"Modalities and special faculties."},{"time":721000,"text":"Now, the human mind is not a single unitary information processor,"},{"time":726000,"text":"but it has a lot of different, special, evolved modules"},{"time":730000,"text":"that do specific things for us."},{"time":732000,"text":"If you think about what we normally take as giving life a lot of its meaning --"},{"time":736000,"text":"music, humor, eroticism, spirituality, aesthetics,"},{"time":740000,"text":"nurturing and caring, gossip, chatting with people --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"all of these, very likely, are enabled by a special circuitry"},{"time":749000,"text":"that we humans have,"},{"time":751000,"text":"but that you could have another intelligent life form that lacks these."},{"time":754000,"text":"We're just lucky that we have the requisite neural machinery"},{"time":757000,"text":"to process music and to appreciate it and enjoy it."},{"time":761000,"text":"All of these would enable, in principle -- be amenable to enhancement."},{"time":764000,"text":"Some people have a better musical ability"},{"time":766000,"text":"and ability to appreciate music than others have."},{"time":768000,"text":"It's also interesting to think about what other things are --"},{"time":771000,"text":"so if these all enabled great values,"},{"time":775000,"text":"why should we think that evolution has happened to provide us"},{"time":778000,"text":"with all the modalities we would need to engage"},{"time":781000,"text":"with other values that there might be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"Imagine a species"},{"time":785000,"text":"that just didn't have this neural machinery for processing music."},{"time":789000,"text":"And they would just stare at us with bafflement"},{"time":792000,"text":"when we spend time listening to a beautiful performance,"},{"time":796000,"text":"like the one we just heard -- because of people making stupid movements,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and they would be really irritated and wouldn't see what we were up to."},{"time":801000,"text":"But maybe they have another faculty, something else"},{"time":804000,"text":"that would seem equally irrational to us,"},{"time":807000,"text":"but they actually tap into some great possible value there."},{"time":810000,"text":"But we are just literally deaf to that kind of value."},{"time":814000,"text":"So we could think of adding on different,"},{"time":816000,"text":"new sensory capacities and mental faculties."},{"time":820000,"text":"Bodily functionality and morphology and affective self-control."},{"time":825000,"text":"Greater subjective well-being."},{"time":827000,"text":"Be able to switch between relaxation and activity --"},{"time":830000,"text":"being able to go slow when you need to do that, and to speed up."},{"time":834000,"text":"Able to switch back and forth more easily"},{"time":836000,"text":"would be a neat thing to be able to do --"},{"time":838000,"text":"easier to achieve the flow state,"},{"time":840000,"text":"when you're totally immersed in something you are doing."},{"time":844000,"text":"Conscientiousness and sympathy."},{"time":846000,"text":"The ability to -- it's another interesting application"},{"time":849000,"text":"that would have large social ramification, perhaps."},{"time":852000,"text":"If you could actually choose to preserve your romantic attachments to one person,"},{"time":858000,"text":"undiminished through time,"},{"time":860000,"text":"so that wouldn't have to -- love would never have to fade if you didn't want it to."},{"time":865000,"text":"That's probably not all that difficult."},{"time":868000,"text":"It might just be a simple hormone or something that could do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"It's been done in voles."},{"time":877000,"text":"You can engineer a prairie vole to become monogamous"},{"time":880000,"text":"when it's naturally polygamous."},{"time":882000,"text":"It's just a single gene."},{"time":884000,"text":"Might be more complicated in humans, but perhaps not that much."},{"time":886000,"text":"This is the last picture that I want to --"},{"time":889000,"text":"now we've got to use the laser pointer."},{"time":892000,"text":"A possible mode of being here would be a way of life --"},{"time":895000,"text":"a way of being, experiencing, thinking, seeing,"},{"time":899000,"text":"interacting with the world."},{"time":901000,"text":"Down here in this little corner, here, we have the little sub-space"},{"time":906000,"text":"of this larger space that is accessible to human beings --"},{"time":910000,"text":"beings with our biological capacities."},{"time":913000,"text":"It's a part of the space that's accessible to animals;"},{"time":916000,"text":"since we are animals, we are a subset of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919000,"text":"And then you can imagine some enhancements of human capacities."},{"time":923000,"text":"There would be different modes of being you could experience"},{"time":926000,"text":"if you were able to stay alive for, say, 200 years."},{"time":929000,"text":"Then you could live sorts of lives and accumulate wisdoms"},{"time":933000,"text":"that are just not possible for humans as we currently are."},{"time":936000,"text":"So then, you move off to this larger sphere of \"human +,\""},{"time":940000,"text":"and you could continue that process and eventually"},{"time":943000,"text":"explore a lot of this larger space of possible modes of being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947000,"text":"Now, why is that a good thing to do?"},{"time":949000,"text":"Well, we know already that in this little human circle there,"},{"time":953000,"text":"there are these enormously wonderful and worthwhile modes of being --"},{"time":957000,"text":"human life at its best is wonderful."},{"time":960000,"text":"We have no reason to believe that within this much, much larger space"},{"time":965000,"text":"there would not also be extremely worthwhile modes of being,"},{"time":969000,"text":"perhaps ones that would be way beyond our wildest ability"},{"time":975000,"text":"even to imagine or dream about."},{"time":977000,"text":"And so, to fix this third problem,"},{"time":979000,"text":"I think we need -- slowly, carefully, with ethical wisdom and constraint --"},{"time":985000,"text":"develop the means that enable us to go out in this larger space and explore it"},{"time":990000,"text":"and find the great values that might hide there."},{"time":992000,"text":"Thanks."}]}]}